Note:
WebAssembly System Interface (WASI) Syscall Platform

Defines all WASI Preview 1 function imports, platform metadata, and registration
logic for the Runa compiler's syscall subsystem. WASI provides a capability-based
system interface for WebAssembly modules, enabling portable access to file I/O,
clocks, random number generation, and process control.

Unlike native platforms, WASI does not use numeric syscall instructions. Instead,
WASI functions are imported from the "wasi_snapshot_preview1" module and invoked
as regular WebAssembly function calls. However, for uniformity within the Runa
compiler's cross-platform syscall infrastructure, each WASI function is assigned
a synthetic syscall number that maps to its position in the WASI specification.

Key differences from native syscall platforms:
- No "syscall" instruction: WASI uses imported function calls
- Pointer size is 4 bytes (wasm32 linear memory)
- Memory management uses memory.grow/memory.size instead of mmap/brk
- File I/O uses iovec-based scatter/gather patterns (fd_read, fd_write)
- Path operations require a pre-opened directory file descriptor (dirfd)
- All WASI functions return an errno value (0 = success)

Calling convention:
- Arguments are passed as wasm32 i32 values on the WebAssembly operand stack
- 64-bit values (offsets, timestamps) are passed as i64
- Return values are written to caller-supplied memory pointers
- The WASI function itself returns an errno code (i32)

This file provides:
1. All WASI Preview 1 function number constants
2. Platform info creation for WASM/WASI
3. Full WASI function registration with argument types and categories
4. Fast name-to-number lookup without requiring a registry instance

Dependencies:
- Imports platform_interface.runa for syscall interface definitions
- Imports syscall_registry.runa for registry registration
- Imports machine_code_interface.runa for architecture/OS constants
:End Note

Import "compiler/backend/syscalls/platforms/platform_interface.runa" as PlatformInterface
Import "compiler/backend/syscalls/syscall_registry.runa" as SyscallRegistry
Import "compiler/backend/machine_code/common/machine_code_interface.runa" as MachineCode
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List

Note: ============================================================================
Note: WASI Preview 1 Function Number Constants
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
WASI Preview 1 functions are defined in the WASI specification:
https://github.com/WebAssembly/WASI/blob/main/phases/snapshot/witx/wasi_snapshot_preview1.witx

Unlike POSIX syscalls, WASI functions do not have kernel-assigned numbers. The
constants below are synthetic identifiers assigned for uniformity within the Runa
compiler's cross-platform syscall registry. They are ordered to match the WASI
specification's canonical ordering.

The selection covers all WASI Preview 1 functions needed by the Runa runtime and
standard library: file descriptor I/O, path operations, process control, clock
access, and random number generation.

WASI uses a capability-based security model where file descriptors carry rights
that determine which operations are permitted. The fs_rights_base and
fs_rights_inheriting parameters on path_open control these capabilities.
@End Reasoning

